
# main categories
```
├─stage_1  
├─stage_2
├─output_dir
├─util
├─s1_main.py	# 第一阶段主函数
├─s2_main.py	# 第二阶段主函数
```
# stage 1
## train 
```python
python main.py \
    --dataset_name RSNA \
    --anomaly_rate 0.6 \
    --class_name bottle \
    --save_freq 200 \
    --blr 1.5e-2 \
    --epochs 500 \
    --batch_size 64 \
```

- `--dataset_name`,  `--anomaly rate` and  `--class_name` are all dataset parameters.
	- `--dataset_name` should be chosen from `{"RSNA", "pretrain", "mvtec"}`. Please pay attention to capitalization. 
	- `--anomaly rate` should only be considered while using `pretrain` dataset, just leave it in other circumstances.  `pretrain` dataset is the combination of RSNA, vinbigdata and chest-xray dataset, containing 87855 images.
	- `--class_name` should only be considered while using `mvtec` dataset.  `mvtec` dataset contains 15 classes in total. If you want to train a model with the whole dataset, please set `class_name` as `"*"`.
- `--save_freq` : model will be saved every `save_freq` epoches.
## outputs
The first stage will only output checkpoint file corresponding to dataset parameters. 
The final structure of `./output_dir` should be as following:
```
├─output_dir
│ ├─RSNA   
│ │ ├─epxxx.pth	# s1 checkpoint based on RSNA
│ │ ├─ ......
│ ├─mvtec  
│ │ ├─bottle	# sample class
│ │ │ ├─epxxx.pth	# s1 checkpoint based on mvtec->bottle
│ │ │ ├─ ......
│ │ ├─ ......	# other classes
│ ├─pretrain	# We do not use "pretrain" dataset in stage 2.
│ │ ├─ 0.2	# sample anomaly rate
│ │ │ ├─epxxx.pth	# s1 checkpoint 
│ │ ├─ ......	# others
```

# stage 2
## mode1: train and evaluate
```python 
python s2_main.py \
	# generate s1 latent
    --s1_chkpt ${S1_CHKPT_DIR} \	# output of stage 1
    --win_size 9 \		# side length of surrounding area (in patches)
    --type_idx 0 \	# *
    --always_generate False \	# *
    --dataset_name RSNA \
    --class_name bottle \
    --source latent \ # "img" or "latent"
	# train s2 model
    --mode train_eval \	# train and evaluate
	## s2 model parameters
    --model_name cls_token_model \	# *
    --depth 4 \	# *
    --mlp_k 4 \	 # *
	## s2 training parameters
    --save_freq 200 \
    --gpu 0 \
    --blr 1.5e-3 \
    --epochs 500 \
    --batch_size 64 \
# * will be shown as below
```
- `type_idx`: settings of padding and dilated convolution. It should be chosen from  `0 to 5`, refering to  `["none", "dilated", "dilated_padding_zero", "dilated_padding_rotate_8", "dilated_padding_rotate_4", "dilated_padding_rotate_2"]` respectively.
- `--always_generate`: it will still generate s1 latent features according to these parameters, even if there exists matched features. You can set it as  `True` when you are not sure those features are correct.
- `--model_name` should be chosen from  `{"cls_token_model", "fc_model"}`. The two models are shown as below.
![avatar][pic1]
![avatar][pic2]
- `--depth` is the number of ViTs of any of the model you chose.
- `--mlp_k` is only used in `cls_token_model`. It is the magnification of MLP.
### outputs
In `train_eval` mode, our model will output corresponding checkpoint file and test result (as `result.xslx`).
The final structure of `output_dir` should be as following:
```
├─output_dir
│ ├─RSNA	# (dataset_name)
│ │ ├─epxxx.pth	# s1 checkpoint
│ │ ├─none	# (type_idx) sample setting of padding and dilated convolution
│ │ │ ├─latent	# (source)
│ │ │ │ ├─cls_token_model-en4-mlp4-ep0-win9.pth	# sample of s2 checkpoint
│ │ │ │ ├─result.xslx		# test result file
│ │ │ ├─img	# (source)
│ │ │ │ ├─cls_token_model-en8-mlp4-ep5-win9.pth	# another sample of s2 checkpoint
│ │ │ │ ├─result.xslx		# test result file
│ │ ├─dilated	# (type_idx) other settings
│ │ ├─ ......
│ ├─mvtec	# similar to above: dataset_name/class_name/type/source
│ │ ├─ ......
│ ├─pretrain	# We do not use "pretrain" dataset in stage 2.
│ │ ├─ ......
```

## mode2: test
```python
python s2_main.py \
    --mode test \
    --s2_chkpt ./output_dir/RSNA/none/img/cls_token_model-en4-mlp4-ep0-win9.pth	# path of s2 checkpoint file you want to test
```
You can just input the file path you want to test. It is because while training, the directory and the file name are named to contain all the nessesary information needed in this mode, such as `dataset_name`, `model_name`, `depth`, etc.
Outputs will be writen into the corresponding `result.xslx`.
